b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Rank Tracker is best suited for SEO professionals, agencies, power users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Surfer SEO, meanwhile, shines for content writers, SEO specialists, agencies, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2004, Rank Tracker describes itself as \"Desktop-based rank tracking and keyword research tool by SEO PowerSuite.\" Surfer SEO, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI-powered content optimization tool for data-driven on-page SEO.\" With 13 years between them, Rank Tracker brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Surfer SEO offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Surfer SEO** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (8 vs 5). However, this does not mean Rank Tracker is a poor choice — far from it. Rank Tracker excels in its own right, particularly for SEO professionals and agencies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class content optimization scoring, go with Surfer SEO. If unlimited keyword tracking on desktop matters more to you, Rank Tracker is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
